[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(23) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Cast off their clothes, and threw dust into the air.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The latter gesture would seem to have been a natural relief, as with other Oriental nations, to the violence of uncontrolled passion. It may be, however, that the handfuls of dust were aimed at the Apostle as a sign of loathing (comp. Notes on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 18:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); and if we take the English version, the “casting off” their outer garments looked very much like preparing for the act of stoning, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:58",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The verb may, however, mean only that they “shook their garments,” as St. Paul had done in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 18:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and so the two gestures might be parts of the same act. On the whole, the latter view seems the more probable.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Acts 22:23-24",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 22:23-24",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And as they cried out ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In this furious manner; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and cast",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " — Or tore; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "off their clothes ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In token of indignation and horror at this pretended blasphemy: or, as Dr. Whitby thinks, as in the case of Stephen, that they might be ready to stone him; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and threw dust into the air ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Through vehemence of rage, which they knew not how to give vent to; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the chief captain ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Not knowing the particulars of what had passed, but perceiving, by the effect, that Paul had rather exasperated than appeased them by the apology which he had been permitted to make, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "commanded ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that he should ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "be brought into the castle, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— As no witnesses were produced in a regular way to give information against him, he ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "bade that he should be examined by scourging ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In order that he might get to know by his own confession, since he could not learn it any other way; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "wherefore they cried so against him — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That the Romans used this method of scourging to compel real or supposed criminals to make confession, is proved by Dr. Lardner, and several other learned writers.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
