        "text": "ἢ καὶ φοβῆσαι βουλόμενοι τὸν ἄρχοντα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Wetstein, Heinrichs, Kuinoel, Hackett, and others explain it of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "waving their garments",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", by which means those at a distance signified their assent to the murderous exclamations of those standing near; and the throwing of the dust at all was only ",
        "children": []
