        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and threw dust into the air",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Compare the action of Shimei, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 16:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the marginal rendering shews that the dust was thrown at David. Perhaps it may have been meant in the present case to be thrown at St Paul, who was above the crowd, at the top of the stairs. The attempt to reach him with what they threw was futile, but it shewed what they would fain have done. For a like action as a sign of grief cp. ",
        "children": []
